This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, which are typically covered in the computer science sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which falls under "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of pre-trained word embeddings and domain adversarial training, which are techniques commonly used in "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) research. The paper also deals with text classification, which is a sub-topic of "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of different models on in-domain and out-of-domain samples, which is relevant to "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) research on domain adaptation.
